  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "We can tailor DBSCAN to reflect RDT by choosing an appropriate ε and MinPts.",
    "ε refers to the maximum distance between two points for one to be considered as in the neighborhood of the other.",
    "This reflects the \"interaction distance\" in RDT, or how close nodes need to be to influence each other.",
    "Relational density Rp in RDT indicates the density of connections within a subset of the network.",
    "DBSCAN's ε parameter can be seen as a threshold for this density."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}